{"word":"πλήν","slug":"πλήν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>πλήν</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Hom.\">Hom.</a> <el>ἔμπλην</el> ‘near, close by’] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adv.\">adv.</a> introducing a modifying or incremental clause in a statement or narrative<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ funct.\">funct.</a> as conjunction <b>rather <a href='B:470 11:22'>Mt 11:22</a>; <a href='B:470 18:7'>18:7</a>; <a href='B:470 26:39'>26:39</a>; <a href='B:490 6:35'>Lk 6:35</a>; <a href='B:490 10:11'>10:11</a>; <a href='B:490 11:41'>11:41</a>; <a href='B:490 12:31'>12:31</a>; <a href='B:490 23:28'>23:28</a>; except (this) <a href='B:730 2:25'>Rv 2:25</a>; on the other hand <a href='B:490 18:8'>Lk 18:8</a>; <a href='B:530 11:11'>1 Cor 11:11</a>; <a href='B:560 5:33'>Eph 5:33</a>; <a href='B:570 3:16'>Phil 3:16</a>; <a href='B:570 4:14'>4:14</a>; as for <a href='B:490 19:27'>Lk 19:27</a>;</b> <el>πλὴν ἰδοῦ</el>, only/just, look! <b><a href='B:490 22:21'>22:21</a>;</b> <el>πλὴν <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὅτι\">ὅτι</a></el> except that <b><a href='B:490 13:33'>13:33</a>; <a href='B:510 20:23'>Ac 20:23</a>;</b> <el>τί <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γάρ\">γάρ</a></el>; <el>πλὴν <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὅτι\">ὅτι</a></el> what’s the outcome? The fact is that <b><a href='B:570 1:18'>Phil 1:18</a>.</b> Adversatively, in apodosis after <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:μέν\">μέν</a></el>, <b>but <a href='B:490 22:22'>Lk 22:22</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ funct.\">funct.</a> as <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prep.\">prep.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ gen.\">gen.</a> <b>except <a href='B:480 12:32'>Mk 12:32</a>; <a href='B:510 8:1'>Ac 8:1</a>; <a href='B:510 15:28'>15:28</a>; <a href='B:510 27:22'>27:22</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:πλήμμυρα\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home